    • Constructor Detail

      • Number

        public Number(long id,
      java.lang.String number,
      int type,
      int unreadMessageCount,
      byte[] publicKey,
      byte[] signature,
      java.lang.Integer enNonceCount,
      java.lang.Integer deNonceCount,
      int initiator,
      int keyExchangeFlag)
        A class used to store information from the numbers table
        Parameters:
        id - The number's sql id.
        number - A number for the contact
        type - The type of number, whether it is a cell, home, etc. For more information of types of numbers please see the DBAccessor class for the 'TYPES' variable
        unreadMessageCount - The number of messages that have not been read from this number
        publicKey - The contact's public key.
        signature - The contact's signature.
        enNonceCount - The encryption nonce count
        deNonceCount - The decryption nonce count
        initiator - Set to false if equal to 0 otherwise true.
        keyExchangeFlag - for how key exchange messages from the contact will be handled
